WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:57.280 --> 02:01.200
- Walk the wall on the left!
- I need a line!

02:07.720 --> 02:12.440
I found her!
I found her!

02:12.480 --> 02:14.360
I need some help
down here!

02:16.480 --> 02:19.360
I need it now!

02:19.480 --> 02:22.440
Anybody hear me?

02:22.560 --> 02:25.280
Get down here now!

02:25.320 --> 02:27.200
Come on!

02:31.320 --> 02:34.600
Shepherd! Burr!

02:34.720 --> 02:37.240
I got her! I can't move!

02:37.320 --> 02:40.480
Come down here now!

02:42.080 --> 02:44.480
Hold on.
They'll be here.

02:44.520 --> 02:47.040
Move!

02:48.680 --> 02:51.200
- I heard a voice.
- Help me!

02:52.720 --> 02:54.840
I can't breathe!

02:54.960 --> 02:59.560
Help me! Help me out!
Help me out!

02:59.720 --> 03:02.680
Help me move it!

03:29.960 --> 03:32.720
Bring up the skycam.
Pan it left.

03:32.800 --> 03:35.120
Show me what God sees.

03:35.200 --> 03:39.280
Okay, camera two, show me the stands.

03:39.400 --> 03:41.600
- Three, give me the ice.
- Okay, graphic is up.

03:41.680 --> 03:43.560
Uh, put game seven on preset.

03:43.600 --> 03:46.000
How many technicians
are gonna be inside the arena?

03:46.120 --> 03:48.320
We got 12 cameramen,
6 support... that's 18.

03:48.400 --> 03:50.280
I want to limit their access.

03:50.320 --> 03:52.640
Technicians and announcers
are the only ones cleared.

03:52.680 --> 03:54.920
Hey, Spota, let us in.

03:55.040 --> 03:58.320
Work don't stop just 'cause the
Vice President's coming, you know, babe.

03:58.400 --> 04:00.240
Must be Republicans.

04:00.320 --> 04:02.640
Having everybody check in through one
gate like this is a pain in the butt.

04:02.720 --> 04:05.040
- It's only one night.
- It's the last game of the Stanley Cup.

04:05.080 --> 04:07.560
Having the Vice President
here turns a headache into a concussion.

04:07.680 --> 04:11.160
- I didn't vote for this guy.
- That's what makes what you're
doin' such a special gesture.

04:21.160 --> 04:23.040
Hello, Pittsburgh.

04:23.080 --> 04:26.880
Here we are in the seventh game of the
Stanley Cup finals. Penguins and Hawks.

04:26.960 --> 04:30.600
Penguins in a come-from-behind
victory to shut down the Hawks.

04:32.520 --> 04:34.120
Shit.

04:37.120 --> 04:39.760
Sorry. Uh, my dog's missing.

04:39.880 --> 04:41.720
We're out looking for him.

04:41.800 --> 04:45.120
- Is it bad?
- What? You think this might be good?

04:45.200 --> 04:47.280
- Let me see your license.
- Oh, sure.

04:47.400 --> 04:49.560
Move. Move.

04:49.680 --> 04:52.000
We are going to steal your car.

04:52.080 --> 04:54.720
Don't get killed over it, huh?

05:21.520 --> 05:24.160
It's the last game.
We got a couple of minutes to go.

05:24.240 --> 05:25.840
Just 15 seconds to go!

05:25.960 --> 05:28.600
He skates up to center.
He knocks down one defender.

05:28.680 --> 05:31.840
He's skating like a madman around
the ice. He gets to the blue line.

05:31.920 --> 05:34.840
He shoots. Whoa!
And he scores! Whoo!

05:34.960 --> 05:38.440
- Scratch my back with a hacksaw...
- Yes!

05:38.560 --> 05:40.480
Dad!

05:40.560 --> 05:42.040
Hey!

05:44.160 --> 05:46.360
- That's a fancy new stick.
- Michael gave it to me.

05:46.440 --> 05:48.640
- Hi.
- How are you, Darren?

05:48.680 --> 05:50.720
Darren, what are you
doing here?

05:50.840 --> 05:53.760
- You can't stay.
We're getting ready to leave.
- It's his birthday.

05:53.840 --> 05:56.040
And you've got him
all day tomorrow.

05:56.160 --> 05:59.080
I just got these.
I thought the kids might wanna...

05:59.200 --> 06:02.080
We're all going out
to dinner.

06:02.200 --> 06:06.280
- Looks like those are Penguin tickets.
- They are.

06:06.400 --> 06:09.120
It's the seventh game.

06:09.200 --> 06:11.200
- Vice President's gonna be there.
- Daddy! Daddy!

06:13.160 --> 06:15.920
- Hey, that's my hat!
- I can wear it. Mom said I could.

06:16.000 --> 06:17.840
I did?

06:19.240 --> 06:21.120
You know what that means?

06:23.320 --> 06:26.080
- Not a clue.
- It means "I love you."

06:27.160 --> 06:29.960
I love you too.

06:30.040 --> 06:33.160
She's practicing to be deaf,
but that's still my hat!

06:33.280 --> 06:37.320
- I'll get you a new one.
- You can't just take them
without talking to me first.

06:37.480 --> 06:40.440
- Besides, you only have two tickets.
- I'm working at the arena.

06:40.520 --> 06:43.880
- You're back to work, Dad?
- He's a fire inspector at the game.

06:44.000 --> 06:47.240
- It's very important work.
- Are you a fireman again, Daddy?

06:47.320 --> 06:50.560
Kind of, yeah.

06:50.640 --> 06:52.520
Kathi tells me it's only temporary.

06:52.640 --> 06:57.160
- He was trying to save a little
girl in a burning building...
- Are we going to the game?

06:59.640 --> 07:01.520
Don't do this again. I mean it.

07:01.600 --> 07:04.600
It's not fair to the kids... or me.

07:04.680 --> 07:06.560
I promise.

08:45.440 --> 08:47.720
Excuse me.

09:02.760 --> 09:05.000
This is Andrew.
He's the head chef.

09:05.120 --> 09:07.160
Nobody goes in that elevator,
and I mean nobody,

09:07.240 --> 09:09.800
even if they have proper I.D.,
unless this man says it's okay.

09:09.920 --> 09:12.000
If he doesn't know them,
they don't get in that elevator.

09:12.120 --> 09:15.480
After you finish the Vice President's
party, this kitchen is closed.

09:15.560 --> 09:17.600
- Have I made myself clear?
- Abundantly.

09:17.680 --> 09:20.200
That's how I like it.
Abundantly.

09:44.040 --> 09:46.240
Mrs. Ferrara?

09:46.320 --> 09:48.200
Yes?

09:48.320 --> 09:51.680
Let's just stroll into your house
like I'm your favorite nephew.

10:08.120 --> 10:11.240
- Ackerman, Ekers.
- Yeah.

10:11.360 --> 10:15.120
Come on, Mac. Mr. McCord makes sure
the building doesn't burn down.

10:15.200 --> 10:18.960
Go on through, Mr. Mac.
And who's this beauty?

10:19.040 --> 10:21.200
This is my daughter Emily
and my son Tyler.

10:21.320 --> 10:24.680
- Want a stamp?
- Love a stamp.

10:24.800 --> 10:27.920
Hey, can you guys play
after we get in?

10:28.000 --> 10:31.400
Hey, hold your horses.
I'm getting a stamp here.

10:31.520 --> 10:33.800
I'll never wash
this hand again.

10:33.880 --> 10:37.000
- See you later, Mr. Mac.
- Okay.

10:48.360 --> 10:50.560
- Joan.
- Hi, Darren.

10:50.640 --> 10:54.080
- Are you working tonight?
- After I take Tyler to the locker room.

10:54.240 --> 10:56.960
Hey, could you give Emily
a look at Icey?

10:57.000 --> 11:00.800
Icey always loves company. Come on,
Emily, I'm gonna show you where Icey is.

11:00.920 --> 11:04.480
Icey. Big deal.
Some fat guy in a ratty penguin suit.

11:04.640 --> 11:08.240
That blonde you're staring at,
she's the fat guy.

11:11.880 --> 11:14.560
- What's he doing?
- Shaping the blade.

11:14.640 --> 11:17.880
They're like horseshoes. You get 'em
hot enough, you can bend 'em.

11:17.960 --> 11:20.800
You, uh, recognize him?

11:20.840 --> 11:23.680
Yeah. Luc Robitaille.

11:23.800 --> 11:26.400
He waved at me.
You see that, Dad?

11:26.560 --> 11:28.360
Luc Robitaille waved at me.

11:28.480 --> 11:30.720
Come on, I'll introduce you.
He won't bite.

11:30.800 --> 11:35.400
- Luc, this is Tyler McCord
and his father Darren.
- Hi, Tyler. How are you?

11:35.520 --> 11:37.320
- Ca va?
- Bonjour.

11:44.000 --> 11:45.880
Dad, what did he say?

11:45.920 --> 11:47.800
He thinks, uh, they're gonna win.

11:47.840 --> 11:50.680
Hey, that's Brad Tolliver!

11:50.760 --> 11:52.960
- Dad, he doesn't have a rocking chair.
- A what?

11:53.040 --> 11:55.840
My dad said you should be sitting in
a rocking chair instead of on the ice.

11:55.880 --> 11:59.040
- Oh, is that so?
- You play hockey, Tyler?

11:59.200 --> 12:01.520
No, but my dad played.
He was a goalie.

12:01.600 --> 12:05.120
A little semi-pro in Canada.
It was a long time ago.

12:05.280 --> 12:07.080
Come by some afternoon.

12:07.200 --> 12:08.760
I'll show you the difference between
the game you played and the one I play.

12:08.800 --> 12:10.360
I'll show you the difference between
the game you played and the one I play.

12:11.240 --> 12:13.280
I can see the difference.

12:29.760 --> 12:31.760
I got this one, man.

12:32.800 --> 12:34.480
Yes.

12:36.400 --> 12:40.280
You boys have fun?

12:40.360 --> 12:43.520
Luc Robitaille talked to me,
and we saw Brad Tolliver close up.

12:43.640 --> 12:45.760
Your friends are gonna
be so jealous of you.

12:45.800 --> 12:48.160
- I wanna go with Icey.
- So does Tyler.

12:48.160 --> 12:51.040
Icey has to hit the stands, guys.
I'll see you later.

12:51.040 --> 12:52.960
Bye-bye.

12:57.760 --> 13:00.960
Andrew, this is Emily and Tyler.

13:01.000 --> 13:03.080
Pleasure.

13:03.120 --> 13:06.360
- Be right back.
- Come. I want to show you something.

13:11.480 --> 13:13.600
Whoa! Cool!

13:13.640 --> 13:16.240
That's why you won't hear
anyone complain about my cooking.

13:16.320 --> 13:18.880
- At least not to my face.
- You got a burnt-out light bulb.

13:18.960 --> 13:22.040
Could you change it?
I've got my hands full.

13:22.120 --> 13:23.960
Sure.

13:24.040 --> 13:27.520
Is that what Daddy does,
change light bulbs?

13:27.640 --> 13:30.680
No, Emily.
He's just helping out.

13:30.760 --> 13:34.080
- Firemen don't do that kind of stuff.
- What kind of stuff?

13:34.160 --> 13:36.920
- Uh, nothing.
- When are we gonna sit down?

14:02.200 --> 14:05.720
Frequent Flyer is in and on
his way to the locker room.

14:05.760 --> 14:07.640
Keep him moving.

14:15.320 --> 14:18.240
The Penguin fans are anxious
to see for the first time...

14:18.320 --> 14:22.040
- the Penguins kicking the Stanley Cup...
- Do you have any cookies?

14:22.080 --> 14:25.280
You force your way in here with a gun,
and now I have to feed you?

14:25.360 --> 14:28.640
You don't have to.
But I still have the gun.

14:30.880 --> 14:33.080
I think I have some Fig Newtons.

14:38.880 --> 14:41.600
Hey! Caution.

14:41.640 --> 14:43.720
Caution keeps you safe.

14:54.280 --> 14:57.440
I keep my machine gun
in with the produce.

14:57.520 --> 15:00.040
Okay, Veep's comin' in.
Let's get decent!

15:00.080 --> 15:02.080
Christ, Jefferson,
it's a locker room.

15:02.200 --> 15:05.280
Duckerman, why don't you
put on a jock?

15:05.360 --> 15:07.920
- Got any tape?
- You're covering the right head.

15:08.000 --> 15:10.320
Let's go, let's go.

15:10.400 --> 15:14.480
All right, guys, I'm privileged to
introduce Vice President Daniel Bender.

15:14.560 --> 15:18.040
He's a big hockey fan
and he'd like to say a few words.

15:18.080 --> 15:20.960
"A few words."
There's an optimist.

15:21.080 --> 15:23.680
I want to wish you all
the best of luck and, uh,

15:23.760 --> 15:25.880
are you Democrats
or Republicans?

15:25.960 --> 15:28.080
Neither, sir. Canadians.

15:28.160 --> 15:31.160
Well, in that case, good luck...

15:31.200 --> 15:34.040
and I hope to toast
your championship after the game.

15:34.120 --> 15:37.080
Sir, are you going to say the
same thing to the Blackhawks?

15:37.160 --> 15:39.920
Of course.
Nice outfit, Duckerman.

15:50.280 --> 15:53.440
Two nights ago with the Blackhawks
on the brink of elimination...

15:53.560 --> 15:56.160
It's time!

15:56.240 --> 15:58.880
I want you to pick up the phone...

15:58.960 --> 16:03.800
and dial 555-1793.

16:05.000 --> 16:07.880
- That's my husband's work number.
- It certainly is.

16:08.960 --> 16:11.480
When you get him on the line,

16:11.560 --> 16:15.400
- say only what's written on this.
- Ohh.

16:18.600 --> 16:21.480
Kitchen. Yeah. Hold on.

16:21.600 --> 16:23.400
Andrew, it's your wife.

16:32.160 --> 16:34.040
- Hello?
- Andy, it...

16:34.080 --> 16:36.800
We have your wife.
Follow her instructions.

16:41.720 --> 16:44.520
They will not hurt me...

16:44.640 --> 16:46.440
if you do as they say.

16:46.560 --> 16:51.160
If you give any indication something
is wrong, they will... kill me.

16:54.600 --> 16:59.720
When you go to the...
Vice President's box,

16:59.800 --> 17:03.400
you will take two new
assistants with you...

17:03.520 --> 17:05.560
escorted by
two security men.

17:05.640 --> 17:09.160
Get them into the box.
That's all you need to do.

17:09.280 --> 17:11.560
That's all you need to know.

17:11.640 --> 17:14.280
Who are these men?
How will I know them?

17:14.359 --> 17:17.160
In 30 seconds, you'll know.

17:17.240 --> 17:19.640
I swear this.
If you hurt my wife, I'll...

17:19.720 --> 17:23.000
You'll what?
Burn my toast?

17:31.880 --> 17:34.360
- Mr. Ferrara?
- Yes?

17:34.440 --> 17:35.960
Are these men yours?

17:41.960 --> 17:45.560
Yes. They're mine.

17:51.080 --> 17:53.720
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.

17:53.800 --> 17:58.760
The National Hockey League presents
game seven of the Stanley Cup finals.

17:58.840 --> 18:03.400
The Chicago Blackhawks
and the Pittsburgh Penguins.

18:05.440 --> 18:08.480
As we get ready for the seventh and
final game of the Stanley Cup finals,

18:08.520 --> 18:11.920
you can feel the electricity in the air;
it sends a chill up your spine, Paul.

18:12.000 --> 18:15.640
One of these clubs is going to
skate with Lord Stanley's cup
here at Civic Arena Ice tonight.

18:18.440 --> 18:20.840
Listen to the crowd, Mike.
They're going crazy.

18:20.960 --> 18:23.200
Well, here's to a great game.

18:23.240 --> 18:27.880
Great if we win;
not so great if we lose.

18:40.640 --> 18:42.520
We are ready.

18:42.600 --> 18:45.600
Thank you, everybody.
You may leave now.

18:45.640 --> 18:47.560
Mr. Ferrara will close up
your stations.

18:57.440 --> 19:00.040
...singing of our National Anthem.

19:00.160 --> 19:05.880
Oh, say, can you see

19:05.920 --> 19:10.080
# By the dawn's
early light

19:10.120 --> 19:14.200
# What so proudly we hailed

19:14.240 --> 19:18.360
# At the twilight's
last gleaming

19:18.400 --> 19:20.920
- # Whose broad stripes
- What the hell are you...

19:21.000 --> 19:23.480
# And bright stars

19:23.560 --> 19:28.000
# Through the perilous fight

19:28.040 --> 19:32.680
# O'er the ramparts
we watched

19:32.800 --> 19:37.480
# Were so gallantly streaming

19:37.560 --> 19:41.760
# And the rockets'
red glare

19:41.880 --> 19:46.960
# The bombs bursting in air

19:47.040 --> 19:51.640
# Gave proof
through the night

19:51.680 --> 19:57.080
# That our flag
was still there

19:57.120 --> 20:00.000
- I love that part.
- # Oh, say does that

20:00.040 --> 20:02.560
- # Star-spangled
- Well, gotta go.

20:02.600 --> 20:08.920
# Banner yet wave

20:09.000 --> 20:12.720
# O'er the land

20:12.800 --> 20:15.680
# Of the free

20:15.760 --> 20:18.280
# And the home

20:18.400 --> 20:22.680
# Of the brave

20:32.360 --> 20:34.240
This place is going crazy right now.

20:34.280 --> 20:38.080
You could not beg, borrow or
steal a ticket before the game tonight.

20:38.120 --> 20:40.120
If you were packing heat,
you couldn't get in here.

20:40.200 --> 20:42.680
Eddie Belfour
starts in goal for Chicago.

20:42.760 --> 20:44.680
Amazingly, Brad Tolliver will play...

20:44.800 --> 20:47.840
even though he could hardly walk today
much less skate with a fever of 104.

20:47.880 --> 20:50.440
And here we go.
Game seven of the Stanley Cup finals.

20:50.560 --> 20:53.080
And the Chicago Blackhawks
control the opening face-off.

20:53.120 --> 20:56.440
They'll work into Pittsburgh territory,
putting pressure on the Penguins early.

20:56.520 --> 20:58.560
Graham, slap shot!
Tolliver makes the save.

21:01.160 --> 21:04.360
Please, he needs a doctor.

21:04.440 --> 21:06.520
No!

21:06.600 --> 21:09.440
Not any more. Go ahead.

21:09.520 --> 21:11.680
Dead heroes get the best funerals.

21:18.080 --> 21:20.360
Thanks for your help, Andrew.

21:22.400 --> 21:26.560
His wife's recently deceased.
He would have been lonely without her.

21:26.680 --> 21:29.680
I hope that clarifies
the urgency of this mission.

21:29.720 --> 21:32.680
Only your best behavior's
gonna be good enough.

21:32.760 --> 21:34.600
That agent's name was Eddie Caline.

21:34.680 --> 21:37.960
He has a 5-year-old boy, a 3-year-old
little girl, and his wife's pregnant.

21:38.080 --> 21:40.360
- I'll send a card.
- What do you want?

21:40.440 --> 21:42.680
What do I want?

21:42.760 --> 21:46.000
World peace, an end to bigotry
and no more mini-malls.

21:47.680 --> 21:49.720
What am I gonna get?

21:49.760 --> 21:52.720
And I am gonna get it.

21:52.800 --> 21:55.160
That, boys and girls,
is really hot.

21:55.200 --> 21:58.240
- What is your objective?
- My objective?

21:58.360 --> 22:02.080
I get funny all over
when you talk like that.

22:02.160 --> 22:03.960
I know what you're thinking.

22:04.000 --> 22:08.680
Evaluate situation, calculate potential
losses and take appropriate action.

22:08.760 --> 22:10.600
Let me do that for you.

22:10.720 --> 22:14.120
The situation is hopeless.
The losses would be unacceptable.

22:14.200 --> 22:17.400
The appropriate action is to do nothing
and keep your fucking mouth shut.

22:17.440 --> 22:20.200
What kind of lunatic are you?

22:20.280 --> 22:23.160
The best kind.

22:23.200 --> 22:26.080
You can keep calling me names
if it makes you feel better.

22:27.280 --> 22:29.240
Throw me your earpiece
and your mike.

22:42.880 --> 22:45.800
Robitaille with a center pass.
That's just gonna miss.

22:45.880 --> 22:49.280
We are still scoreless in game seven,
period one, the Hawks and Pens.

22:53.920 --> 22:56.600
Watch Loeman.
He's got eyes in the back of his head.

22:57.640 --> 22:59.640
They must be closed.

23:01.160 --> 23:03.200
- Oh, gross!
- I have some work to do.

23:03.240 --> 23:06.080
I'll be back before the period ends.
You two stay right here.

23:06.120 --> 23:08.120
I'll go too,
so you'll have company.

23:08.200 --> 23:10.760
Thanks, sweetheart,
but you stay with Tyler.

23:12.680 --> 23:15.040
Now you won't be by yourself.

23:15.120 --> 23:16.960
Thank you.

23:18.640 --> 23:22.480
I mean it. Don't leave your seats.
Oh. In case you want a soda.

23:22.560 --> 23:26.360
- Don't get out of your seats to get it.
- We get the idea, Dad.

23:26.440 --> 23:28.440
Hey, what's that?

23:29.480 --> 23:31.360
Nothing.

23:45.000 --> 23:47.000
What's Daddy gotta do?

23:47.120 --> 23:48.960
Probably change more light bulbs.

23:49.040 --> 23:51.520
You said firemen don't do
that kind of stuff.

23:51.560 --> 23:53.960
Dad's not really
a fireman any more, Emily.

23:55.840 --> 23:58.680
Now a steal by Stevens.
He walks into the Chicago end.

23:58.760 --> 24:01.000
Slap shot!
He... shoots and scores!

24:01.080 --> 24:04.040
Kevin Stevens gives the Penguins
the opening goal.

24:05.760 --> 24:09.640
Get in the fast lane, Grandma.
The bingo game is ready to roll.

24:18.400 --> 24:20.760
Hey!

24:20.840 --> 24:23.160
He doesn't know whether
to cry or wind his watch.

24:23.200 --> 24:25.320
Hey!

24:25.400 --> 24:29.240
- The Penguins have scored.
- Hey!

24:29.320 --> 24:34.160
That one came off Steve Smith, the
Chicago defenseman, and finds the net.

24:34.240 --> 24:37.360
Pittsburgh goal,
his 11th in the play-offs...

24:37.440 --> 24:40.360
scored by number 25,

24:40.440 --> 24:43.120
Kevin Stevens!

24:43.200 --> 24:46.120
Face-off at center ice.
Naslund of the Penguins controls.

24:46.200 --> 24:50.000
He jumps into the Chicago end with the
Penguins leading 1-0 here in game seven.

24:50.080 --> 24:53.240
Mike, as we expected,
the hitting has been ferocious.

24:53.320 --> 24:56.120
Uh, if the smoke bothers anyone,
you just speak up.

24:56.200 --> 24:58.760
There's no reason to kill anyone else.
Nobody's a threat to you.

25:02.160 --> 25:04.960
You know, I voted for you.
I really did.

25:05.040 --> 25:08.320
It's your sincerity
and your compassion.

25:08.360 --> 25:11.400
You happen to be wrong, though. There
