Just moments away, they're gonna pack up
the Stanley Cup and take it to Chicago.

01:22:12.760 --> 01:22:15.640
Intercepted by Chicago!

01:22:15.720 --> 01:22:18.920
Big check on
John Cullen of the Penguins.

01:22:25.800 --> 01:22:30.840
Jagr going for the net, Naslund shoots,
and he's stopped by Belfour.

01:22:36.920 --> 01:22:39.760
A minute, thirty-five to go
in the third period.

01:22:39.800 --> 01:22:42.920
That's all that remains
for Chicago to win the Stanley Cup.

01:22:43.000 --> 01:22:45.840
The Penguins need a rally
to tie the game.

01:22:45.920 --> 01:22:48.280
Penguins reach in the corner.

01:22:49.760 --> 01:22:52.680
Drop it.

01:23:08.160 --> 01:23:11.000
Oh, what a save!

01:23:11.040 --> 01:23:15.280
Larmer drills one! Nice stop! He gave
more moves than Mae West on that one!

01:23:15.360 --> 01:23:19.040
One minute remaining
in the third period.

01:23:19.040 --> 01:23:22.680
And the Penguins
trailing by a goal.

01:23:22.720 --> 01:23:25.240
Chicago still
putting pressure on.

01:23:26.800 --> 01:23:30.640
Forty seconds remaining now.

01:23:31.960 --> 01:23:34.000
Aaah!

01:23:35.320 --> 01:23:37.960
The Penguins
need a goal desperately.

01:23:38.040 --> 01:23:41.640
Thirty seconds left. Chicago's looking
for the parade down Michigan Ave.

01:23:41.720 --> 01:23:43.800
They feel they've got
the Stanley Cup.

01:23:48.640 --> 01:23:51.000
Aaah!

01:23:59.680 --> 01:24:01.600
Aaah!

01:24:01.640 --> 01:24:03.520
...Chicago win the Stanley Cup.

01:24:03.560 --> 01:24:06.520
Time again ticking down.
Penguins running out of it.

01:24:07.800 --> 01:24:12.120
Penguins reaching for every
possible thing they have.

