The puck's run by Francis,
ahead to Robitaille.

01:24:21.440 --> 01:24:24.040
Not much time to go. Luc Robitaille...

01:24:30.280 --> 01:24:33.720
We've got eight seconds left!

01:24:38.080 --> 01:24:40.000
Seconds to go.

01:24:57.600 --> 01:24:59.480
Stop the press!
Stop the press!

01:24:59.520 --> 01:25:01.400
The Penguins have tied the game.

01:25:01.440 --> 01:25:05.720
We're going to sudden death overtime!
You would have to be here to believe it!

01:25:05.800 --> 01:25:10.680
Lucky Luc has scored for the Penguins
with under a second to go!

01:25:15.320 --> 01:25:19.040
This series has been incredible!

01:25:19.120 --> 01:25:21.840
- Lucky Luc has done it again!
- Sudden death?

01:25:21.880 --> 01:25:24.120
Sudden death.

01:25:24.200 --> 01:25:27.840
Paul, the Penguins
would not give up, despite the odds.

01:25:27.960 --> 01:25:32.240
Belfour tried everything
in his power to stop them.

01:25:32.280 --> 01:25:36.080
The Penguins have forced
sudden death overtime.

01:25:36.160 --> 01:25:40.440
The team that scores first in the
next period will win the Stanley Cup!

01:25:40.520 --> 01:25:42.840
Pittsburgh goal,

01:25:42.960 --> 01:25:46.000
his 14th in the play-offs,
scored by...

01:25:46.080 --> 01:25:48.880
Life's just a shitbox
of ironies, huh?

01:25:48.960 --> 01:25:51.960
We still got money to move.
I hope it's not mine.

01:25:52.040 --> 01:25:53.880
Everybody's got
a little more time.

01:25:53.960 --> 01:25:56.800
I'd hate to see them waste it.

01:25:56.840 --> 01:25:58.720
Wouldn't you?

01:27:33.720 --> 01:27:37.040
Throw away the clocks, because the next
goal is going to win the Stanley Cup.

01:27:37.080 --> 01:27:38.960
That's what sudden death
is all about.

